<paragraph id="645C36D7FFBEE016FF3D4D86FE29D63C" blockId="25.[144,759,1002,1360]" lastBlockId="26.[164,778,1024,1077]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="696" pageId="25" pageNumber="695">
<emphasis id="5697EAC5FFBEE015FF3D4D86FDFBD609" box="[144,523,1002,1024]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="695">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName id="A3E34D54FFBEE015FEBA4D87FDFBD609" authorityName="Vari &amp; Santana &amp; Wosiacki" authorityYear="2012" box="[279,523,1002,1024]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sternopygidae" genus="Archolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gymnotiformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="695" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="santosi">Archolaemus santosi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is diagnosed from 
<taxonomicName id="A3E34D54FFBEE015FF3D4A64FF2FD614" authorityName=", Schwassmann &amp; Carvalho" authorityYear="1985" box="[144,223,1032,1054]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sternopygidae" genus="Archolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gymnotiformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="695" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blax">
<emphasis id="5697EAC5FFBEE015FF3D4A64FF2FD614" box="[144,223,1032,1054]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="695">A. blax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the length of the gape (the rictus falling short of the vertical through the posterior border of the posterior naris versus extending beyond that line), the depth of the caudal filament (6.7–9.1% CL versus 5.0–6.5% CL), the form of the premaxilla (the anteroposterior length equal to the transverse width versus the anteroposterior length greater than the transverse width), and the length of the posterior ceratohyal (approximately the same length as the ventral hypohyal versus 1.5 times the length of the ventral hypohyal). 
<taxonomicName id="A3E34D54FFBEE015FEC34B57FDACD759" authorityName="Vari &amp; Santana &amp; Wosiacki" authorityYear="2012" box="[366,604,1338,1360]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sternopygidae" genus="Archolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gymnotiformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="695" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="santosi">
<emphasis id="5697EAC5FFBEE015FEC34B57FDACD759" box="[366,604,1338,1360]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="695">Archolaemus santosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed from 
<taxonomicName id="A3E34D54FFBEE015FCC54EABFC14D2D2" authorityName="Vari &amp; Santana &amp; Wosiacki" authorityYear="2012" box="[872,996,198,219]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sternopygidae" genus="Archolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gymnotiformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="695" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferreirai">
<emphasis id="5697EAC5FFBEE015FCC54EABFC14D2D2" box="[872,996,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="695">A. ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the form of the premaxilla (the anteroposterior length equal to the transverse width versus the anteroposterior length greater than the transverse width) and the length of the coronomeckelian bone (less than 20% the length of Meckel’s cartilage versus 50% or more the length of Meckel’s cartilage). 
<taxonomicName id="A3E34D54FFBEE015FC074F10FB6FD39A" authorityName="Vari &amp; Santana &amp; Wosiacki" authorityYear="2012" box="[938,1183,381,403]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sternopygidae" genus="Archolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gymnotiformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="695" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="santosi">
<emphasis id="5697EAC5FFBEE015FC074F10FB6FD39A" box="[938,1183,381,403]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="695">Archolaemus santosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed from 
<taxonomicName id="A3E34D54FFBEE015FC8B4FF1FC7ED3BB" authorityName="Vari &amp; Santana &amp; Wosiacki" authorityYear="2012" box="[806,910,412,434]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sternopygidae" genus="Archolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gymnotiformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="695" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="janeae">
<emphasis id="5697EAC5FFBEE015FC8B4FF1FC7ED3BB" box="[806,910,412,434]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="695">A. janeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the head length to the rear of the opercle (15.0–16.3% LEA versus 13.5–14.7% LEA), the mouth width (7.0–10.3% HL versus 11.0–19.1% HL), the form of the premaxilla (the anteroposterior length equal to the transverse width versus the anteroposterior length greater than the transverse width), the distribution of the teeth on the dentary (dentition restricted to the anterior one-half or slightly more of the dorsal margin versus occupying most of the dorsal margin), and the length of the posterior ceratohyal (approximately the same length as the ventral hypohyal versus 1.5 times the length of the ventral hypohyal). 
<taxonomicName id="A3E34D54FFBEE015FC2F4D66FB71D128" authorityName="Vari &amp; Santana &amp; Wosiacki" authorityYear="2012" box="[898,1153,779,801]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sternopygidae" genus="Archolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gymnotiformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="695" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="santosi">
<emphasis id="5697EAC5FFBEE015FC2F4D66FB71D128" box="[898,1153,779,801]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="695">Archolaemus santosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed from 
<taxonomicName id="A3E34D54FFBEE015FC8B4D47FC78D136" authorityName="Vari &amp; Santana &amp; Wosiacki" authorityYear="2012" box="[806,904,810,831]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sternopygidae" genus="Archolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gymnotiformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="695" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis id="5697EAC5FFBEE015FC8B4D47FC78D136" box="[806,904,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="695">A. luciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the length of the gape (the rictus falling short of the vertical through the posterior border of the posterior nares versus extending beyond that line), the length of the caudal filament (14.4– 27.0% LEA versus 28.6–46.1% LEA), the depth of the caudal filament (6.7–9.1% CL versus 3.3–4.8% CL), the form of the premaxilla (the anteroposterior length equal to the transverse width versus the anteroposterior length greater than the transverse width), and the length of the coronomeckelian bone (less than 20% the length of Meckel’s cartilage versus 50% or more of the length of Meckel’s cartilage). 
<taxonomicName id="A3E34D54FFBEE015FB544A17FC86D6A6" authorityName="Vari &amp; Santana &amp; Wosiacki" authorityYear="2012" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sternopygidae" genus="Archolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gymnotiformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="695" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="santosi">
<emphasis id="5697EAC5FFBEE015FB544A17FC86D6A6" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="695">Archolaemus santosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed from 
<taxonomicName id="A3E34D54FFBEE015FBE24AF4FB2AD6A7" authorityName="Vari &amp; Santana &amp; Wosiacki" authorityYear="2012" box="[1103,1242,1177,1198]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sternopygidae" genus="Archolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gymnotiformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="695" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="5697EAC5FFBEE015FBE24AF4FB2AD6A7" box="[1103,1242,1177,1198]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="695">A. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the pigmentation pattern (the presence of a narrow dark stripe along the lateral line and a broad band of dusky to dark pigmentation overlying the basal pterygiophores of the anal fin versus the lack of such dark pigmentation), the total number of pectoral-fin rays (19–21 versus 16), and the total number of anal-fin rays (204–221 versus 164–186).
</paragraph>
